Found inHis Structural studies of protein-nucleic acid interaction, 1993: CIP t.p. (Thomas A. Steitz; Dept. of Molecular Biophysics & Biochem. & Howard Hughes Medical Inst., Yale Univ.)

New York times WWW site, viewed Oct. 11, 2018 (in obituary published Oct. 10: Thomas A. Steitz; b. Thomas Arthur Steitz, Aug. 23, 1940, Milwaukee; moved with his family to Wauwatosa, Wis. when he was 9; d. Tuesday [Oct. 9, 2018], Branford, Conn., aged 78; towering figure of late-20th-century science who shared a Nobel Prize in Chemistry in 2009 for figuring out the structure of the ribosome, a huge molecule central to translating the genetic code into the proteins that make up living matter)
